ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, the MCDs preparation at room temperature and in atmosphere was proposed (

                     Scheme 1
                     ). Employing o-PDA as a precursor and DMF as solvent, the addition of different oxidants and polyol or polybasic acid leads to the MCDs, respectively, emitting blue, green, yellow and red color. Structural characterization and optical property were performed to investigate the formation and optical mechanisms. The MCDs are formed using energy from oxidation, Schiff base and amidation reaction. Meanwhile, particle size, graphitization and conjugated systems all have significant effects on the color of MCDs by tuning the band gap, which coincides well with the result from the theoretical calculation. Finally, the MCDs/PVP compositions were successfully applied in LEDs fabrication with satisfying optical properties.
